  14 |     | import {Initializable} from "../../proxy/utils/Initializable.sol";
  15 |     | 
  16 |     | /**
  17 |     |  * @dev Implementation of the basic standard multi-token.
  18 |     |  * See https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155
  19 |     |  * Originally based on code by Enjin: https://github.com/enjin/erc-1155
  20 |     |  */
  21 |     | abstract contract ERC1155Upgradeable is Initializable, ContextUpgradeable, ERC165Upgradeable, IERC1155, IERC1155MetadataURI, IERC1155Errors {
  22 |     |     using Arrays for uint256[];
  23 |     |     using Arrays for address[];
  24 |     | 
  25 |     |     /// @custom:storage-location erc7201:openzeppelin.storage.ERC1155
  26 |     |     struct ERC1155Storage {
  27 |     |         mapping(uint256 id => mapping(address account => uint256)) _balances;
  28 |     | 
  29 |     |         mapping(address account => mapping(address operator => bool)) _operatorApprovals;
  30 |     | 
  31 |     |         // Used as the URI for all token types by relying on ID substitution, e.g. https://token-cdn-domain/{id}.json
  32 |     |         string _uri;
  33 |     |     }
  34 |     | 
  35 |     |     // keccak256(abi.encode(uint256(keccak256("openzeppelin.storage.ERC1155")) - 1)) & ~bytes32(uint256(0xff))
  36 |     |     bytes32 private constant ERC1155StorageLocation = 0x88be536d5240c274a3b1d3a1be54482fd9caa294f08c62a7cde569f49a3c4500;
  37 |     | 
  38 |     |     function _getERC1155Storage() private pure returns (ERC1155Storage storage $) {
  39 |     |         assembly {
  40 |     |             $.slot := ERC1155StorageLocation
  41 |     |         }
  42 |     |     }
  43 |     | 
  44 |     |     /**
  45 |     |      * @dev See {_setURI}.
  46 |     |      */
  47 |     |     function __ERC1155_init(string memory uri_) internal onlyInitializing {
  48 |     |         __ERC1155_init_unchained(uri_);
  49 |     |     }
  50 |     | 
  51 |     |     function __ERC1155_init_unchained(string memory uri_) internal onlyInitializing {
  52 |     |         _setURI(uri_);
  53 |     |     }
  54 |     | 
  55 |     |     /**
  56 |     |      * @dev See {IERC165-supportsInterface}.
  57 |     |      */
  58 |     |     function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId) public view virtual override(ERC165Upgradeable, IERC165) returns (bool) {
  59 |     |         return
  60 |     |             interfaceId == type(IERC1155).interfaceId ||
  61 |     |             interfaceId == type(IERC1155MetadataURI).interfaceId ||
  62 |     |             super.supportsInterface(interfaceId);
  63 |     |     }
  64 |     | 
  65 |     |     /**
  66 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}.
  67 |     |      *
  68 |     |      * This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies
  69 |     |      * on the token type ID substitution mechanism
  70 |     |      * https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the ERC].
  71 |     |      *
  72 |     |      * Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the
  73 |     |      * actual token type ID.
  74 |     |      */
  75 |     |     function uri(uint256 /* id */) public view virtual returns (string memory) {
  76 |     |         ERC1155Storage storage $ = _getERC1155Storage();
  77 |     |         return $._uri;
  78 |     |     }
  79 |     | 
  80 |     |     /**
  81 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155-balanceOf}.
  82 |     |      */
  83 |     |     function balanceOf(address account, uint256 id) public view virtual returns (uint256) {
  84 |     |         ERC1155Storage storage $ = _getERC1155Storage();
  85 |     |         return $._balances[id][account];
  86 |     |     }
  87 |     | 
  88 |     |     /**
  89 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}.
  90 |     |      *
  91 |     |      * Requirements:
  92 |     |      *
  93 |     |      * - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.
  94 |     |      */
  95 |     |     function balanceOfBatch(
  96 |     |         address[] memory accounts,
  97 |     |         uint256[] memory ids
  98 |     |     ) public view virtual returns (uint256[] memory) {
  99 |     |         if (accounts.length != ids.length) {
 100 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidArrayLength(ids.length, accounts.length);
 101 |     |         }
 102 |     | 
 103 |     |         uint256[] memory batchBalances = new uint256[](accounts.length);
 104 |     | 
 105 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < accounts.length; ++i) {
 106 |     |             batchBalances[i] = balanceOf(accounts.unsafeMemoryAccess(i), ids.unsafeMemoryAccess(i));
 107 |     |         }
 108 |     | 
 109 |     |         return batchBalances;
 110 |     |     }
 111 |     | 
 112 |     |     /**
 113 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155-setApprovalForAll}.
 114 |     |      */
 115 |     |     function setApprovalForAll(address operator, bool approved) public virtual {
 116 |     |         _setApprovalForAll(_msgSender(), operator, approved);
 117 |     |     }
 118 |     | 
 119 |     |     /**
 120 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155-isApprovedForAll}.
 121 |     |      */
 122 |     |     function isApprovedForAll(address account, address operator) public view virtual returns (bool) {
 123 |     |         ERC1155Storage storage $ = _getERC1155Storage();
 124 |     |         return $._operatorApprovals[account][operator];
 125 |     |     }
 126 |     | 
 127 |     |     /**
 128 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155-safeTransferFrom}.
 129 |     |      */
 130 |     |     function safeTransferFrom(address from, address to, uint256 id, uint256 value, bytes memory data) public virtual {
 131 |     |         address sender = _msgSender();
 132 |     |         if (from != sender && !isApprovedForAll(from, sender)) {
 133 |     |             revert ERC1155MissingApprovalForAll(sender, from);
 134 |     |         }
 135 |     |         _safeTransferFrom(from, to, id, value, data);
 136 |     |     }
 137 |     | 
 138 |     |     /**
 139 |     |      * @dev See {IERC1155-safeBatchTransferFrom}.
 140 |     |      */
 141 |     |     function safeBatchTransferFrom(
 142 |     |         address from,
 143 |     |         address to,
 144 |     |         uint256[] memory ids,
 145 |     |         uint256[] memory values,
 146 |     |         bytes memory data
 147 |     |     ) public virtual {
 148 |     |         address sender = _msgSender();
 149 |     |         if (from != sender && !isApprovedForAll(from, sender)) {
 150 |     |             revert ERC1155MissingApprovalForAll(sender, from);
 151 |     |         }
 152 |     |         _safeBatchTransferFrom(from, to, ids, values, data);
 153 |     |     }
 154 |     | 
 155 |     |     /**
 156 |     |      * @dev Transfers a `value` amount of tokens of type `id` from `from` to `to`. Will mint (or burn) if `from`
 157 |     |      * (or `to`) is the zero address.
 158 |     |      *
 159 |     |      * Emits a {TransferSingle} event if the arrays contain one element, and {TransferBatch} otherwise.
 160 |     |      *
 161 |     |      * Requirements:
 162 |     |      *
 163 |     |      * - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement either {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received}
 164 |     |      *   or {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived} and return the acceptance magic value.
 165 |     |      * - `ids` and `values` must have the same length.
 166 |     |      *
 167 |     |      * NOTE: The ERC-1155 acceptance check is not performed in this function. See {_updateWithAcceptanceCheck} instead.
 168 |     |      */
 169 |     |     function _update(address from, address to, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory values) internal virtual {
 170 |     |         ERC1155Storage storage $ = _getERC1155Storage();
 171 |     |         if (ids.length != values.length) {
 172 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidArrayLength(ids.length, values.length);
 173 |     |         }
 174 |     | 
 175 |     |         address operator = _msgSender();
 176 |     | 
 177 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < ids.length; ++i) {
 178 |     |             uint256 id = ids.unsafeMemoryAccess(i);
 179 |     |             uint256 value = values.unsafeMemoryAccess(i);
 180 |     | 
 181 |     |             if (from != address(0)) {
 182 |     |                 uint256 fromBalance = $._balances[id][from];
 183 |     |                 if (fromBalance < value) {
 184 |     |                     revert ERC1155InsufficientBalance(from, fromBalance, value, id);
 185 |     |                 }
 186 |     |                 unchecked {
 187 |     |                     // Overflow not possible: value <= fromBalance
 188 |     |                     $._balances[id][from] = fromBalance - value;
 189 |     |                 }
 190 |     |             }
 191 |     | 
 192 |     |             if (to != address(0)) {
 193 |     |                 $._balances[id][to] += value;
 194 |     |             }
 195 |     |         }
 196 |     | 
 197 |     |         if (ids.length == 1) {
 198 |     |             uint256 id = ids.unsafeMemoryAccess(0);
 199 |     |             uint256 value = values.unsafeMemoryAccess(0);
 200 |     |             emit TransferSingle(operator, from, to, id, value);
 201 |     |         } else {
 202 |     |             emit TransferBatch(operator, from, to, ids, values);
 203 |     |         }
 204 |     |     }
 205 |     | 
 206 |     |     /**
 207 |     |      * @dev Version of {_update} that performs the token acceptance check by calling
 208 |     |      * {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received} or {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived} on the receiver address if it
 209 |     |      * contains code (eg. is a smart contract at the moment of execution).
 210 |     |      *
 211 |     |      * IMPORTANT: Overriding this function is discouraged because it poses a reentrancy risk from the receiver. So any
 212 |     |      * update to the contract state after this function would break the check-effect-interaction pattern. Consider
 213 |     |      * overriding {_update} instead.
 214 |     |      */
 215 |     |     function _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(
 216 |     |         address from,
 217 |     |         address to,
 218 |     |         uint256[] memory ids,
 219 |     |         uint256[] memory values,
 220 |     |         bytes memory data
 221 |     |     ) internal virtual {
 222 |     |         _update(from, to, ids, values);
 223 |     |         if (to != address(0)) {
 224 |     |             address operator = _msgSender();
 225 |     |             if (ids.length == 1) {
 226 |     |                 uint256 id = ids.unsafeMemoryAccess(0);
 227 |     |                 uint256 value = values.unsafeMemoryAccess(0);
 228 |     |                 ERC1155Utils.checkOnERC1155Received(operator, from, to, id, value, data);
 229 |     |             } else {
 230 |     |                 ERC1155Utils.checkOnERC1155BatchReceived(operator, from, to, ids, values, data);
 231 |     |             }
 232 |     |         }
 233 |     |     }
 234 |     | 
 235 |     |     /**
 236 |     |      * @dev Transfers a `value` tokens of token type `id` from `from` to `to`.
 237 |     |      *
 238 |     |      * Emits a {TransferSingle} event.
 239 |     |      *
 240 |     |      * Requirements:
 241 |     |      *
 242 |     |      * - `to` cannot be the zero address.
 243 |     |      * - `from` must have a balance of tokens of type `id` of at least `value` amount.
 244 |     |      * - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received} and return the
 245 |     |      * acceptance magic value.
 246 |     |      */
 247 |     |     function _safeTransferFrom(address from, address to, uint256 id, uint256 value, bytes memory data) internal {
 248 |     |         if (to == address(0)) {
 249 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidReceiver(address(0));
 250 |     |         }
 251 |     |         if (from == address(0)) {
 252 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidSender(address(0));
 253 |     |         }
 254 |     |         (uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory values) = _asSingletonArrays(id, value);
 255 |     |         _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(from, to, ids, values, data);
 256 |     |     }
 257 |     | 
 258 |     |     /**
 259 |     |      * @dev xref:ROOT:erc1155.adoc#batch-operations[Batched] version of {_safeTransferFrom}.
 260 |     |      *
 261 |     |      * Emits a {TransferBatch} event.
 262 |     |      *
 263 |     |      * Requirements:
 264 |     |      *
 265 |     |      * - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived} and return the
 266 |     |      * acceptance magic value.
 267 |     |      * - `ids` and `values` must have the same length.
 268 |     |      */
 269 |     |     function _safeBatchTransferFrom(
 270 |     |         address from,
 271 |     |         address to,
 272 |     |         uint256[] memory ids,
 273 |     |         uint256[] memory values,
 274 |     |         bytes memory data
 275 |     |     ) internal {
 276 |     |         if (to == address(0)) {
 277 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidReceiver(address(0));
 278 |     |         }
 279 |     |         if (from == address(0)) {
 280 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidSender(address(0));
 281 |     |         }
 282 |     |         _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(from, to, ids, values, data);
 283 |     |     }
 284 |     | 
 285 |     |     /**
 286 |     |      * @dev Sets a new URI for all token types, by relying on the token type ID
 287 |     |      * substitution mechanism
 288 |     |      * https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the ERC].
 289 |     |      *
 290 |     |      * By this mechanism, any occurrence of the `\{id\}` substring in either the
 291 |     |      * URI or any of the values in the JSON file at said URI will be replaced by
 292 |     |      * clients with the token type ID.
 293 |     |      *
 294 |     |      * For example, the `https://token-cdn-domain/\{id\}.json` URI would be
 295 |     |      * interpreted by clients as
 296 |     |      * `https://token-cdn-domain/000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000004cce0.json`
 297 |     |      * for token type ID 0x4cce0.
 298 |     |      *
 299 |     |      * See {uri}.
 300 |     |      *
 301 |     |      * Because these URIs cannot be meaningfully represented by the {URI} event,
 302 |     |      * this function emits no events.
 303 |     |      */
 304 |     |     function _setURI(string memory newuri) internal virtual {
 305 |     |         ERC1155Storage storage $ = _getERC1155Storage();
 306 |     |         $._uri = newuri;
 307 |     |     }
 308 |     | 
 309 |     |     /**
 310 |     |      * @dev Creates a `value` amount of tokens of type `id`, and assigns them to `to`.
 311 |     |      *
 312 |     |      * Emits a {TransferSingle} event.
 313 |     |      *
 314 |     |      * Requirements:
 315 |     |      *
 316 |     |      * - `to` cannot be the zero address.
 317 |     |      * - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received} and return the
 318 |     |      * acceptance magic value.
 319 |     |      */
 320 |     |     function _mint(address to, uint256 id, uint256 value, bytes memory data) internal {
 321 |     |         if (to == address(0)) {
 322 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidReceiver(address(0));
 323 |     |         }
 324 |     |         (uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory values) = _asSingletonArrays(id, value);
 325 |     |         _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(address(0), to, ids, values, data);
 326 |     |     }
 327 |     | 
 328 |     |     /**
 329 |     |      * @dev xref:ROOT:erc1155.adoc#batch-operations[Batched] version of {_mint}.
 330 |     |      *
 331 |     |      * Emits a {TransferBatch} event.
 332 |     |      *
 333 |     |      * Requirements:
 334 |     |      *
 335 |     |      * - `ids` and `values` must have the same length.
 336 |     |      * - `to` cannot be the zero address.
 337 |     |      * - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived} and return the
 338 |     |      * acceptance magic value.
 339 |     |      */
 340 |     |     function _mintBatch(address to, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory values, bytes memory data) internal {
 341 |     |         if (to == address(0)) {
 342 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidReceiver(address(0));
 343 |     |         }
 344 |     |         _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(address(0), to, ids, values, data);
 345 |     |     }
 346 |     | 
 347 |     |     /**
 348 |     |      * @dev Destroys a `value` amount of tokens of type `id` from `from`
 349 |     |      *
 350 |     |      * Emits a {TransferSingle} event.
 351 |     |      *
 352 |     |      * Requirements:
 353 |     |      *
 354 |     |      * - `from` cannot be the zero address.
 355 |     |      * - `from` must have at least `value` amount of tokens of type `id`.
 356 |     |      */
 357 |     |     function _burn(address from, uint256 id, uint256 value) internal {
 358 |     |         if (from == address(0)) {
 359 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidSender(address(0));
 360 |     |         }
 361 |     |         (uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory values) = _asSingletonArrays(id, value);
 362 |     |         _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(from, address(0), ids, values, "");
 363 |     |     }
 364 |     | 
 365 |     |     /**
 366 |     |      * @dev xref:ROOT:erc1155.adoc#batch-operations[Batched] version of {_burn}.
 367 |     |      *
 368 |     |      * Emits a {TransferBatch} event.
 369 |     |      *
 370 |     |      * Requirements:
 371 |     |      *
 372 |     |      * - `from` cannot be the zero address.
 373 |     |      * - `from` must have at least `value` amount of tokens of type `id`.
 374 |     |      * - `ids` and `values` must have the same length.
 375 |     |      */
 376 |     |     function _burnBatch(address from, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory values) internal {
 377 |     |         if (from == address(0)) {
 378 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidSender(address(0));
 379 |     |         }
 380 |     |         _updateWithAcceptanceCheck(from, address(0), ids, values, "");
 381 |     |     }
 382 |     | 
 383 |     |     /**
 384 |     |      * @dev Approve `operator` to operate on all of `owner` tokens
 385 |     |      *
 386 |     |      * Emits an {ApprovalForAll} event.
 387 |     |      *
 388 |     |      * Requirements:
 389 |     |      *
 390 |     |      * - `operator` cannot be the zero address.
 391 |     |      */
 392 |     |     function _setApprovalForAll(address owner, address operator, bool approved) internal virtual {
 393 |     |         ERC1155Storage storage $ = _getERC1155Storage();
 394 |     |         if (operator == address(0)) {
 395 |     |             revert ERC1155InvalidOperator(address(0));
 396 |     |         }
 397 |     |         $._operatorApprovals[owner][operator] = approved;
 398 |     |         emit ApprovalForAll(owner, operator, approved);
 399 |     |     }
 400 |     | 
 401 |     |     /**
 402 |     |      * @dev Creates an array in memory with only one value for each of the elements provided.
 403 |     |      */
 404 |     |     function _asSingletonArrays(
 405 |     |         uint256 element1,
 406 |     |         uint256 element2
 407 |     |     ) private pure returns (uint256[] memory array1, uint256[] memory array2) {
 408 |     |         assembly ("memory-safe") {
 409 |     |             // Load the free memory pointer
 410 |     |             array1 := mload(0x40)
 411 |     |             // Set array length to 1
 412 |     |             mstore(array1, 1)
 413 |     |             // Store the single element at the next word after the length (where content starts)
 414 |     |             mstore(add(array1, 0x20), element1)
 415 |     | 
 416 |     |             // Repeat for next array locating it right after the first array
 417 |     |             array2 := add(array1, 0x40)
 418 |     |             mstore(array2, 1)
 419 |     |             mstore(add(array2, 0x20), element2)
 420 |     | 
 421 |     |             // Update the free memory pointer by pointing after the second array
 422 |     |             mstore(0x40, add(array2, 0x40))
 423 |     |         }
 424 |     |     }
 425 |     | }
 426 |     | 

/home/aman/Desktop/Fuzz data/one-world-fuzz/lib/openzeppelin-contracts-upgradeable/contracts/utils/ContextUpgradeable.sol
  1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
  2 |     | // OpenZeppelin Contracts (last updated v5.0.1) (utils/Context.sol)
  3 |     | 
  4 |     | pragma solidity ^0.8.20;
  5 |     | import {Initializable} from "../proxy/utils/Initializable.sol";
  6 |     | 
  7 |     | /**
  8 |     |  * @dev Provides information about the current execution context, including the
  9 |     |  * sender of the transaction and its data. While these are generally available
 10 |     |  * via msg.sender and msg.data, they should not be accessed in such a direct
 11 |     |  * manner, since when dealing with meta-transactions the account sending and
 12 |     |  * paying for execution may not be the actual sender (as far as an application
 13 |     |  * is concerned).
 14 |     |  *
 15 |     |  * This contract is only required for intermediate, library-like contracts.
 16 |     |  */
 17 |     | abstract contract ContextUpgradeable is Initializable {
 18 |     |     function __Context_init() internal onlyInitializing {
 19 |     |     }
 20 |     | 
 21 |     |     function __Context_init_unchained() internal onlyInitializing {
 22 |     |     }
 23 |     |     function _msgSender() internal view virtual returns (address) {
 24 |     |         return msg.sender;
 25 |     |     }
 26 |     | 
 27 |     |     function _msgData() internal view virtual returns (bytes calldata) {
 28 |     |         return msg.data;
 29 |     |     }
 30 |     | 
 31 |     |     function _contextSuffixLength() internal view virtual returns (uint256) {
 32 |     |         return 0;
 33 |     |     }
 34 |     | }
 35 |     | 

/home/aman/Desktop/Fuzz data/one-world-fuzz/lib/openzeppelin-contracts-upgradeable/contracts/utils/introspection/ERC165Upgradeable.sol
  1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
  2 |     | // OpenZeppelin Contracts (last updated v5.1.0) (utils/introspection/ERC165.sol)
  3 |     | 
  4 |     | pragma solidity ^0.8.20;
  5 |     | 
  6 |     | import {IERC165} from "@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/introspection/IERC165.sol";
  7 |     | import {Initializable} from "../../proxy/utils/Initializable.sol";
  8 |     | 
  9 |     | /**
 10 |     |  * @dev Implementation of the {IERC165} interface.
 11 |     |  *
 12 |     |  * Contracts that want to implement ERC-165 should inherit from this contract and override {supportsInterface} to check
 13 |     |  * for the additional interface id that will be supported. For example:
 14 |     |  *
 15 |     |  * ```solidity
 16 |     |  * function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId) public view virtual override returns (bool) {
 17 |     |  *     return interfaceId == type(MyInterface).interfaceId || super.supportsInterface(interfaceId);
 18 |     |  * }
 19 |     |  * ```
 20 |     |  */
 21 |     | abstract contract ERC165Upgradeable is Initializable, IERC165 {
 22 |     |     function __ERC165_init() internal onlyInitializing {
 23 |     |     }
 24 |     | 
 25 |     |     function __ERC165_init_unchained() internal onlyInitializing {
 26 |     |     }
 27 |     |     /**
 28 |     |      * @dev See {IERC165-supportsInterface}.
 29 |     |      */
 30 |     |     function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId) public view virtual returns (bool) {
 31 |     |         return interfaceId == type(IERC165).interfaceId;
 32 |     |     }
 33 |     | }

   1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
   2 |     | // Compatible with OpenZeppelin Contracts ^5.0.0
   3 |     | pragma solidity 0.8.22;
   4 |     | 
   5 |     | import "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC1155/ERC1155.sol";
   6 |     | import "@openzeppelin/contracts/access/AccessControl.sol";
   7 |     | import "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC1155/extensions/ERC1155Burnable.sol";
   8 |     | import "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC1155/extensions/ERC1155Supply.sol";
   9 |     | import {NativeMetaTransaction} from "./meta-transaction/NativeMetaTransaction.sol";
  10 |     | import "@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Strings.sol";
  11 |     | 
  12 |     | contract OWPIdentity is ERC1155, AccessControl, ERC1155Burnable, ERC1155Supply, NativeMetaTransaction {
  13 |     |     bytes32 public constant MINTER_ROLE = keccak256("MINTER_ROLE");
  14 |     |     using Strings for uint256;
  15 |     |     string public name = "One World Project";
  16 |     |     string public symbol = "OWP";
  17 |     | 
  18 |     |     constructor(address defaultAdmin, address minter, string memory newUri) ERC1155(newUri) {
  19 |     |         _grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, defaultAdmin);
  20 |     |         _grantRole(MINTER_ROLE, minter);
  21 |     |     }
  22 |     | 
  23 |     |     function setURI(string memory newuri) public onlyRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE) {
  24 |     |         _setURI(newuri);
  25 |     |     }
  26 |     | 
  27 |     |     function uri(uint256 tokenId) public view virtual override returns (string memory) {
  28 |     |         return string.concat(super.uri(tokenId), tokenId.toString());
  29 |     |     }
  30 |     | 
  31 |     |     function mint(address account, uint256 id, uint256 amount, bytes memory data)
  32 |     |         public
  33 |     |         onlyRole(MINTER_ROLE)
  34 |     |     {
  35 |     |         _mint(account, id, amount, data);
  36 |     |     }
  37 |     | 
  38 |     |     function mintBatch(address to, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory amounts, bytes memory data)
  39 |     |         public
  40 |     |         onlyRole(MINTER_ROLE)
  41 |     |     {
  42 |     |         _mintBatch(to, ids, amounts, data);
  43 |     |     }
  44 |     | 
  45 |     |     function burn(address account, uint256 id, uint256 amount)
  46 |     |         public override
  47 |     |         onlyRole(MINTER_ROLE)
  48 |     |     {
  49 |     |         _burn(account, id, amount);
  50 |     |     }
  51 |     | 
  52 |     |     function burnBatch(address to, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory amounts)
  53 |     |         public override
  54 |     |         onlyRole(MINTER_ROLE) // @audit : add a burner role to burn nfts
  55 |     |     {
  56 |     |         _burnBatch(to, ids, amounts);
  57 |     |     }
  58 |     | 
  59 |     |     function burnBatchMultiple(address[] memory tos, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory amounts)
  60 |     |         public
  61 |     |         onlyRole(MINTER_ROLE)
  62 |     |     {
  63 |     |         require(tos.length == ids.length, "Invalid input");
  64 |     |         require(amounts.length == ids.length, "Invalid input");
  65 |     | 
  66 |     |         for(uint256 i = 0; i < tos.length; i++){
  67 |     |             _burn(tos[i], ids[i], amounts[i]);            
  68 |     |         }
  69 |     |     }
  70 |     | 
  71 |     |     // The following functions are overrides required by Solidity.
  72 |     |     function _update(
  73 |     |         address from,
  74 |     |         address to,
  75 |     |         uint256[] memory ids,
  76 |     |         uint256[] memory amounts
  77 |     |     ) internal virtual override(ERC1155, ERC1155Supply){
  78 |     |         require(from == address(0) || to == address(0), "OWPIdentity: NFT Not transferrable.");
  79 |     |         super._update(from, to, ids, amounts);
  80 |     |     }
  81 |     | 
  82 |     |     function _msgSender()
  83 |     |         internal
  84 |     |         view
  85 |     |         override
  86 |     |         returns (address sender)
  87 |     |     {
  88 |     |         if (msg.sender == address(this)) {
  89 |     |             bytes memory array = msg.data;
  90 |     |             uint256 index = msg.data.length;
  91 |     |             assembly {
  92 |     |                 // Load the 32 bytes word from memory with the address on the lower 20 bytes, and mask those.
  93 |     |                 sender := and(
  94 |     |                     mload(add(array, index)),
  95 |     |                     0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff
  96 |     |                 )
  97 |     |             }
  98 |     |         } else {
  99 |     |             sender = msg.sender;
 100 |     |         }
 101 |     |         return sender;
 102 |     |     }
 103 |     | 
 104 |     |     function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId)
 105 |     |         public
 106 |     |         view
 107 |     |         override(ERC1155, AccessControl)
 108 |     |         returns (bool)
 109 |     |     {
 110 |     |         return super.supportsInterface(interfaceId);
 111 |     |     }
 112 |     | }

   9 |     | /**
  10 |     |  * @title CurrencyManager
  11 |     |  * @notice It allows adding/removing currencies for usage on the OneWP.
  12 |     |  */
  13 | *   | contract CurrencyManager is ICurrencyManager, AccessControl {
  14 |     |   error CurrencyManagerError(string message);
  15 |     |   using EnumerableSet for EnumerableSet.AddressSet;
  16 |     | 
  17 |     |   EnumerableSet.AddressSet private _whitelistedCurrencies;
  18 |     | 
  19 | *   |   bytes32 public constant ADMIN_ROLE = keccak256("ADMIN_ROLE");
  20 |     | 
  21 |     |   event CurrencyRemoved(address indexed currency);
  22 |     |   event CurrencyWhitelisted(address indexed currency);
  23 |     | 
  24 |     |   constructor() {
  25 |     |     _grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, msg.sender);
  26 |     |     _grantRole(ADMIN_ROLE, msg.sender);
  27 |     |   }
  28 |     | 
  29 |     |   /**
  30 |     |    * @notice Add a currency in the system
  31 |     |    * @param currency address of the currency to add
  32 |     |    */
  33 | *   |   function addCurrency(
  34 |     |     address currency
  35 |     |   ) external override onlyRole(ADMIN_ROLE) {
  36 | *   |     if (currency == address(0))
  37 |     |       revert CurrencyManagerError("Cannot be null address");
  38 | *   |     if (_whitelistedCurrencies.contains(currency))
  39 |     |       revert CurrencyManagerError("Already whitelisted");
  40 | *   |     _whitelistedCurrencies.add(currency);
  41 |     | 
  42 | *   |     emit CurrencyWhitelisted(currency);
  43 |     |   }
  44 |     | 
  45 |     |   /**
  46 |     |    * @notice Remove a currency from the system
  47 |     |    * @param currency address of the currency to remove
  48 |     |    */
  49 |     |   function removeCurrency(
  50 |     |     address currency
  51 |     |   ) external override onlyRole(ADMIN_ROLE) {
  52 |     |     if (!_whitelistedCurrencies.contains(currency))
  53 |     |       revert CurrencyManagerError("Not whitelisted");
  54 |     |     _whitelistedCurrencies.remove(currency);
  55 |     | 
  56 |     |     emit CurrencyRemoved(currency);
  57 |     |   }
  58 |     | 
  59 |     |   /**
  60 |     |    * @notice Returns if a currency is in the system
  61 |     |    * @param currency address of the currency
  62 |     |    */
  63 | *   |   function isCurrencyWhitelisted(
  64 |     |     address currency
  65 | *   |   ) external view override returns (bool) {
  66 | *   |     return _whitelistedCurrencies.contains(currency);
  67 |     |   }
  68 |     | 
  69 |     |   /**
  70 |     |    * @notice View number of whitelisted currencies
  71 |     |    */
  72 |     |   function viewCountWhitelistedCurrencies()
  73 |     |     external
  74 |     |     view
  75 |     |     override
  76 |     |     returns (uint256)
  77 |     |   {
  78 |     |     return _whitelistedCurrencies.length();
  79 |     |   }
  80 |     | 
  81 |     |   /**
  82 |     |    * @notice See whitelisted currencies in the system
  83 |     |    * @param cursor cursor (should start at 0 for first request)
  84 |     |    * @param size size of the response (e.g., 50)
  85 |     |    */
  86 |     |   function viewWhitelistedCurrencies(
  87 |     |     uint256 cursor,
  88 |     |     uint256 size
  89 |     |   ) external view override returns (address[] memory, uint256) {
  90 |     |     uint256 length = size;
  91 |     | 
  92 |     |     if (length > _whitelistedCurrencies.length() - cursor) {
  93 |     |       length = _whitelistedCurrencies.length() - cursor;
  94 |     |     }
  95 |     | 
  96 |     |     address[] memory whitelistedCurrencies = new address[](length);
  97 |     | 
  98 |     |     for (uint256 i = 0; i < length; i++) {
  99 |     |       whitelistedCurrencies[i] = _whitelistedCurrencies.at(cursor + i);
 100 |     |     }
 101 |     | 
 102 |     |     return (whitelistedCurrencies, cursor + length);
 103 |     |   }
 104 |     | }

 138 |     |             interfaceId == type(IMembershipERC1155).interfaceId ||
 139 |     |             super.supportsInterface(interfaceId);

 142 |     |     /// @notice Claim profits accumulated from the profit pool
 143 |     |     /// @return profit The amount of profit claimed
 144 |     |     function claimProfit() external returns (uint256 profit) {
 145 |     |         profit = saveProfit(msg.sender);
 146 |     |         require(profit > 0, "No profit available");
 147 |     |         savedProfit[msg.sender] = 0;
 148 |     |         IERC20(currency).safeTransfer(msg.sender, profit);
 149 |     |         emit Claim(msg.sender, profit);
 150 |     |     }
 151 |     | 
 152 |     |     /// @notice View profit for an account
 153 |     |     /// @param account The account to query
 154 |     |     /// @return The total profit amount for the account
 155 |     |     function profitOf(address account) external view returns (uint256) {
 156 |     |         return savedProfit[account] + getUnsaved(account);
 157 |     |     }
 158 |     | 
 159 |     |     /// @notice Calculates unsaved profits for an account
 160 |     |     /// @param account The account to query
 161 |     |     /// @return profit The unsaved profit amount
 162 | *   |     function getUnsaved(address account) internal view returns (uint256 profit) {
 163 | *   |         return ((totalProfit - lastProfit[account]) * shareOf(account)) / ACCURACY;
 164 |     |     }
 165 |     | 
 166 |     |     /// @notice Calculates the share of total profits for an account
 167 |     |     /// @param account The account to query
 168 |     |     /// @return The weighted share of the account
 169 | *   |     function shareOf(address account) public view returns (uint256) {
 170 | *   |         return (balanceOf(account, 0) * 64) +
 171 | *   |                (balanceOf(account, 1) * 32) +
 172 | *   |                (balanceOf(account, 2) * 16) +
 173 | *   |                (balanceOf(account, 3) * 8) +
 174 | *   |                (balanceOf(account, 4) * 4) +
 175 | *   |                (balanceOf(account, 5) * 2) +
 176 | *   |                balanceOf(account, 6);
 177 |     |     }

 189 |     |     /// @notice Distributes profits to token holders
 190 |     |     /// @param amount The amount of currency to distribute
 191 |     |     function sendProfit(uint256 amount) external {
 192 |     |         uint256 _totalSupply = totalSupply;
 193 |     |         if (_totalSupply > 0) {
 194 |     |             totalProfit += (amount * ACCURACY) / _totalSupply;
 195 |     |             IERC20(currency).safeTransferFrom(msg.sender, address(this), amount);
 196 |     |             emit Profit(amount);
 197 |     |         } else {
 198 |     |             IERC20(currency).safeTransferFrom(msg.sender, creator, amount); // Redirect profit to creator if no supply
 199 |     |         }
 200 |     |     }

 218 |     |     function callExternalContract(address contractAddress, bytes memory data) external payable onlyRole(OWP_FACTORY_ROLE) returns (bytes memory ) {
 219 |     |         (bool success, bytes memory returndata) = contractAddress.call{value: msg.value}(data);

/home/aman/Desktop/Fuzz data/one-world-fuzz/src/meta-transaction/EIP712Base.sol
  1 |     | 
  2 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
  3 |     | pragma solidity 0.8.22;
  4 |     | 
  5 |     | 
  6 |     | contract EIP712Base {
  7 |     |     struct EIP712Domain {
  8 |     |         string name;
  9 |     |         string version;
 10 |     |         address verifyingContract;
 11 |     |         bytes32 salt;
 12 |     |     }
 13 |     | 
 14 |     |     bytes32 internal constant EIP712_DOMAIN_TYPEHASH = keccak256(
 15 |     |         bytes(
 16 |     |             "EIP712Domain(string name,string version,address verifyingContract,bytes32 salt)"
 17 |     |         )
 18 |     |     );
 19 |     |     bytes32 internal domainSeperator;
 20 |     | 
 21 |     |     constructor(
 22 |     |         string memory name,
 23 |     |         string memory version
 24 |     |     ){
 25 |     |         _setDomainSeperator(name, version);
 26 |     |     }
 27 |     | 
 28 |     |     function _setDomainSeperator(string memory name, string memory version) internal {
 29 |     |         domainSeperator = keccak256(
 30 |     |             abi.encode(
 31 |     |                 EIP712_DOMAIN_TYPEHASH,
 32 |     |                 keccak256(bytes(name)),
 33 |     |                 keccak256(bytes(version)),
 34 |     |                 address(this),
 35 |     |                 bytes32(getChainId())
 36 |     |             )
 37 |     |         );
 38 |     |     }
 39 |     | 
 40 |     |     function getDomainSeperator() public view returns (bytes32) {
 41 |     |         return domainSeperator;
 42 |     |     }
 43 |     | 
 44 |     |     function getChainId() public view returns (uint256) {
 45 |     |         uint256 id;
 46 |     |         assembly {
 47 |     |             id := chainid()
 48 |     |         }
 49 |     |         return id;
 50 |     |     }
 51 |     | 
 52 |     |     /**
 53 |     |      * Accept message hash and returns hash message in EIP712 compatible form
 54 |     |      * So that it can be used to recover signer from signature signed using EIP712 formatted data
 55 |     |      * https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-712
 56 |     |      * "\\x19" makes the encoding deterministic
 57 |     |      * "\\x01" is the version byte to make it compatible to EIP-191
 58 |     |      */
 59 |     |     function toTypedMessageHash(bytes32 messageHash)
 60 |     |         internal
 61 |     |         view
 62 |     |         returns (bytes32)
 63 |     |     {
 64 |     |         return
 65 |     |             keccak256(
 66 |     |                 abi.encodePacked("\x19\x01", getDomainSeperator(), messageHash)
 67 |     |             );
 68 |     |     }
 69 |     | }
 70 |     | 

/home/aman/Desktop/Fuzz data/one-world-fuzz/src/meta-transaction/NativeMetaTransaction.sol
   1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
   2 |     | 
   3 |     | pragma solidity 0.8.22;
   4 |     | import { EIP712Base } from "./EIP712Base.sol";
   5 |     | 
   6 |     | contract NativeMetaTransaction is EIP712Base {
   7 |     |     bytes32 private constant META_TRANSACTION_TYPEHASH = keccak256(
   8 |     |         bytes(
   9 |     |             "MetaTransaction(uint256 nonce,address from,bytes functionSignature)"
  10 |     |         )
  11 |     |     );
  12 |     |     event MetaTransactionExecuted(
  13 |     |         address userAddress,
  14 |     |         address relayerAddress,
  15 |     |         bytes functionSignature,
  16 |     |         bytes32 metaTXHash
  17 |     |     );
  18 |     |     mapping(address => uint256) nonces;
  19 |     | 
  20 |     |     /*
  21 |     |      * Meta transaction structure.
  22 |     |      * No point of including value field here as if user is doing value transfer then he has the funds to pay for gas
  23 |     |      * He should call the desired function directly in that case.
  24 |     |      */
  25 |     |     struct MetaTransaction {
  26 |     |         uint256 nonce;
  27 |     |         address from;
  28 |     |         bytes functionSignature;
  29 |     |     }
  30 |     | 
  31 |     |     constructor() EIP712Base('OWP','1'){}
  32 |     | 
  33 |     |     function executeMetaTransaction(
  34 |     |         address userAddress,
  35 |     |         bytes memory functionSignature,
  36 |     |         bytes32 sigR,
  37 |     |         bytes32 sigS,
  38 |     |         uint8 sigV
  39 |     |     ) public payable returns (bytes memory) {
  40 |     |         MetaTransaction memory metaTx = MetaTransaction({
  41 |     |             nonce: nonces[userAddress],
  42 |     |             from: userAddress,
  43 |     |             functionSignature: functionSignature
  44 |     |         });
  45 |     | 
  46 | *   |         require(
  47 |     |             verify(userAddress, metaTx, sigR, sigS, sigV),
  48 |     |             "Signer and signature do not match"
  49 |     |         );
  50 |     | 
  51 |     |         // increase nonce for user (to avoid re-use)
  52 |     |         nonces[userAddress] = nonces[userAddress] + 1;
  53 |     | 
  54 |     |         emit MetaTransactionExecuted(
  55 |     |             userAddress,
  56 |     |             msg.sender,
  57 |     |             functionSignature,
  58 |     |             hashMetaTransaction(metaTx)
  59 |     |         );
  60 |     | 
  61 |     |         // Append userAddress and relayer address at the end to extract it from calling context
  62 |     |         (bool success, bytes memory returnData) = address(this).call{value: msg.value}(
  63 |     |             abi.encodePacked(functionSignature, userAddress)
  64 |     |         );
  65 |     |         require(success, "Function call not successful");
  66 |     | 
  67 |     |         return returnData; // return bob
  68 |     |     }
  69 |     | 
  70 |     |     function hashMetaTransaction(MetaTransaction memory metaTx)
  71 |     |         public
  72 |     |         pure
  73 |     |         returns (bytes32)
  74 |     |     {
  75 |     |         return
  76 |     |             keccak256(
  77 |     |                 abi.encode(
  78 |     |                     META_TRANSACTION_TYPEHASH,
  79 |     |                     metaTx.nonce,
  80 |     |                     metaTx.from,
  81 |     |                     keccak256(metaTx.functionSignature)
  82 |     |                 )
  83 |     |             );
  84 |     |     }
  85 |     | 
  86 |     |     function getNonce(address user) public view returns (uint256 nonce) {
  87 |     |         nonce = nonces[user];
  88 |     |     }
  89 |     | 
  90 |     |     function verify(
  91 |     |         address signer,
  92 |     |         MetaTransaction memory metaTx,
  93 |     |         bytes32 sigR,
  94 |     |         bytes32 sigS,
  95 |     |         uint8 sigV
  96 |     |     ) internal view returns (bool) {
  97 |     |         require(signer != address(0), "NativeMetaTransaction: INVALID_SIGNER");
  98 |     |         return
  99 |     |             signer ==
 100 |     |             ecrecover(
 101 |     |                 toTypedMessageHash(hashMetaTransaction(metaTx)),
 102 |     |                 sigV,
 103 |     |                 sigR,
 104 |     |                 sigS
 105 |     |             );
 106 |     |     }
 107 |     | }
 108 |     |
